				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Compairing Bsts to mages is a serious case of apple's to oranges imo. For one thing in terms of class balance bst pets pre 62 are in their 40's in lvl. Mage pets at 49 are in that range. For another mages get pets from lvl 5 and every 4-5 lvls their after till 51 where we get pets till 54. Bsts get new pets at 9-15-22-30-39-49. After that at 54 and every 2 lvls their after. I play both class's and honestly I'm alittle puzzled about the class envy problem. Mages send their pets and blow things up. Bsts send their pets, cast a few spells then charge into the frey or exsclusively pet cleric and cast some offensive spells. Bsts melee better then mages. To that I can only say duh. However bsts spells are pathetic compaired to mage castings. At lvl 49 the bst nuke a bst has does 300 points of damage. Thier best dot does 45 points a tick second best does 27 a tick and their slow does 22%. Yes their pets have a 102 point disease based dd proc if/when it lands the pet itself has about 2100hp and does about 53 damage w/ a 17 point bash. Mage pets hit for about 58 kicks or bash's for 23 and has about 3K hp if memory serves. Mages best nukes do 810 damage and our rain does 324 a wave. Lastly consider the fact mages have gotten new pets at 44 which bsts did not and you wonder why bsts have been given the ability to heal their pets? Oh and for what it's worth their Spiritual light does 3hp/3mana a tick regen and their best pc heal does 100hp. Beastlords are alot of fun imo but so are mages, they are just different and personally I think they deserve better heals since they get worse pets.<br />_________________<br />Member of the guild Wings of Valor on the E-marr server.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
