<br />
You say apples and oranges, then compare extremes. Mages nuke, BL Melees. BOTH HEAL. The most important thing to consider when upgrading/adding spells is class balance. Better pet heals would help a mage solo, but not really help in groups, as pet is usually not tanking. Mages have to choices for XP, Solo (Pre pop mostly, pop is not very easy), or DPS spot in a group. Beast's have 3, although one is a backup role more then anything. Solo (Slow +Heals allows a BST to solo in pre/post PoP), 2. DPS spot, 3. Slower while looking for a primary slower/backup slower (They have a very low mana slow).  I don't include tanking, although a 61 bst guildie was tanking in PoI Factory, cause we had a gimptastic pally. I don't include that as BST is not a class you grab when you need a tank, lol.  Mage/BST Heals only play into the solo equation. 
<br />

<br />
I do not  want to be a beastlord, but I want to be able to heal my pet effectivly, as I have most of the levels. Mages cannot do that now, and have a very hard/slow time soloing in PoP. I don't want BST nerfed, they are a fellow pet class, and BST/Mages working together are great.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=542302" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://myweb.cableone.net/nweaver/gryyf.jpg" border="0" /></a>
