				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yes, increasing the rate in which mages heal their pet would make them more comparable to beastlords, however the reverse is also true. Increase the beastlords nukes and you'll improve their ability to solo to be comprable to a mage. Mages higher dps in my opinion offsets the beastlords ability to pet heal. While soloing it has been my experience with my beastlord that I don't enter melee much, as honestly my self healing spells aren't very good. They are comparable to the mage pet heals to be honest.  Beastlords ability to heal thier pets doesn't normally effect their group roles as they or someone else is normally tanking. As for xp bsts can group and in doing so add a dps slot or try and solo. As for the backup slower, I don't know any raid that would want to settle on a 22% or even a 30% slow on a significant encounter. In conclussion I think that after considering this discussion my opinion has become more solid in that the two class's are actually fairly well balanced to each other. They both are excellent damage dealing class's they just go about it in different ways in.<br />_________________<br />Member of the guild Wings of Valor on the E-marr server.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
