				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In my opinion chain casting pets isn't really a viable method for xping for a beastlord. With the casting times of thier pets being at lvl 56 14 seconds, 58 16 seconds and lvl 60 11 seconds. That is before the 3 seconds for the pet proc spell the 6.5 seconds for the pet haste and not including giving the pet any other buffs. Beastlords heals however is 7.5 seconds for a 1250 heal which in that lvl range is about 1/2 the pets life. For hunting in tier one pop you also have to consider that at this lvl beastlord pets are lvl 43 through 47 at lvl's 55 to 60 for the beastlord. The level disparidy between the pop mobs and beastlord pets fairly ensures problems with taunt as well as their procs and general ability to hit, much for the same reason people don't like using the mage epic pet in the planes though that pet is much better then a beastlords warder.
<br />

<br />
 By comparison mages get 2 heals at lvl 44. A heal over time Primal remedy which does 480points over 36 seconds costing 200 mana and refresh summoning which heals 379points for 200 mana. Btw that said I recant something I said earlier, mages can heal their pets much better then beastlords can heal themselves it's not anywhere near close.
<br />

<br />

<br />
 Also thought it would be worth mentioning. At this lvl range the best heal spell beastlords have is a 580 point heal which with both of these heal spells I feel puts mages on more then equitable ground.
<br />

<br />
 Anyhow at 52 mages get Transon's elemental infusion a 580point heal for 275 mana and finally at 60 receive Transons elemental renewal a 900 point heal for 400 mana. Personally I think your best shot for receiving a heal spell would be to request a heal over time spell for around lvl 54 something that heals for around 800hp.<br />_________________<br />Member of the guild Wings of Valor on the E-marr server.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
